  "body": "I mistakenly gave containerd-ctr 0.2.3 an out of date OCI `config.json`.\r\nIt would be nice if containerd could validate versions and provide an error/warning message if the versions don't align, instead of only the unmarshal error:\r\n\r\n``` \r\n# containerd-ctr --version\r\nctr version 0.2.3 commit: 3addd840653146c90a254301d6c3a663c7fd6429\r\n# containerd-ctr containers start --no-pivot --attach rngd /containers/rngd\r\nFATA[0000] json: cannot unmarshal array into Go struct field Process.capabilities of type specs.LinuxCapabilities \r\n```\r\n\r\nFrom talking with @crosbymichael, he suggests \"unable to unmarshal, current supported runtime-spec is x.x.x but provided with x.x.o\" and that would be very helpful \ud83d\udc4d ",
